reviews.review_text: Phil ! thank you for freeing the music whoever you are!!

kudoos archive! thanks to the archive and GD prod. for posting this board after commercial release
 of course its killer '73, all that needs to be said
HCS The best Here Comes Sunshine and a really nice entire show. The boys were on!

Playin' like a wave upon the sand..  The Here Comes Sunshine and the PITB
make this one of the better 1st sets of 73.
Couple that with the 2nd set from the previous night 12/18
and you have some mighty sweet Tampa GD.
To my ear the 12/18 just has a mellower vibe all around
but hey this 1973 where any one set is capable of outshining the entire output of a 3 night run post Brent/Bruce.
Sure wish there was a New Year's Eve run for 1973
but the band certainly deserved the downtime.
I like living on the West Coast of Florida it is certainly much more laid back then the North East fed big city vibe of the East Coast of Florida
Everything o.k. til I got ambushed by that OTHER ONE
an END of the World TOO or at least life as we know it
Thank G-d for the Stella Blue :)
